🚀 Excited to Share My HR Data Analysis Project! 🚀

I’m thrilled to announce the completion of my HR Data Analysis Project as part of my internship with NSDIC! Using Power BI, I transformed raw HR data into actionable insights, creating an interactive dashboard to help organizations make data-driven decisions.

📊 What I Did:

 a. Analyzed employee headcount by job role.

 b. Explored gender distribution and salary discrepancies.

 c. Identified the highest earners and examined the relationship between qualifications and salaries.

 d. Conducted a detailed leave balance analysis.

 e. Built a streamlined HR dashboard for quick and insightful decision-making.

🛠️ Tools Used:

 1. Power BI (for data visualization and dashboard creation)

 2. MS Excel (for data cleaning and preparation)

 3. DAX (for advanced calculations)

🔑 Key Insights:

 a. Discovered trends in salary distribution across roles.

 b. Identified gender diversity gaps in certain departments.

 c. Highlighted the impact of qualifications on employee salaries.
